  991. def allInstances[T <: UMLElement[Uml]](metaclassType: scala.reflect.api.JavaUniverse.Type, metaclass2umlOTI: scala.reflect.api.JavaUniverse.MethodSymbol, umlOTIType: scala.reflect.api.JavaUniverse.Type, scope: Option[UMLElement[Uml]])(implicit umlTag: scala.reflect.api.JavaUniverse.TypeTag[Uml], typ: scala.reflect.api.JavaUniverse.TypeTag[T]): Option[Set[T]]

    The MagicDraw-specific equivalent of OCL T.allInstances() for an OTI adapter T of an OMG UML metaclass

    The MagicDraw-specific equivalent of OCL T.allInstances() for an OTI adapter T of an OMG UML metaclass

    It is unclear what is the proper way to do the OCL equivalent of T.allInstances() with the MagicDraw API. The logic below is based on what is available in the MagicDraw Open API.

    T

    A MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter for an OMG UML metaclass

    metaclassType

    A MagicDraw Open API metaclass corresponding to an OMG UML metaclass

    metaclass2umlOTI

    The OTI uml<metaclass>() converter method to map a MagicDraw metaclass instance to a corresponding MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter instance

    umlOTIType

    A MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter corresponding to an OMG UML metaclasss

    scope

    An OTI UML element scoping the result of the instances of the OTI UML metaclasses to look for, or None for a global query

    umlTag

    Scala type information about the MagicDraw-specific OTI metaclass adaptation trait

    typ

    Scala type information about a MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter

    returns

    The MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter instances corresponding to MagicDraw-specific instances of a MagicDraw-specific implementation of MagicDraw-specific OTI adapter for an OMG UML metaclass

    Definition Classes
    MagicDrawUMLUtil → UMLOps
    See also

    https://support.nomagic.com/browse/MDUMLCS-16937
